TCP prevents receivers from becoming overwhelmed using a receive window (rwnd).

The sliding window determines how much unacknowledged data may be transmitted before waiting for acknowledgements.

Important terms include:

SF – Send First
SN – Send Next
RN – Receive Next
RF – Receive First
rwnd – Receiver Window
Cybersecurity Relevance

Attackers may abuse TCP window behavior during denial-of-service attacks or use unusual window sizes for operating system fingerprinting.

Tools
Wireshark
Nmap
Zeek

Blue Team (Defenders)

Process: Monitor abnormal TCP window behavior, detect fingerprinting attempts, and investigate unusual traffic patterns.

End Goal: Identify reconnaissance activity and prevent resource exhaustion attacks.

Red Team (Attackers)

Process: Analyze TCP window characteristics to infer operating systems or exploit inefficient flow control during attacks.

End Goal: Gather intelligence and optimize exploitation strategies.
